16 Sep 2017 09:08






Yes and no.

What everyone remembers as the  movie (with Tim Curry as Pennywise) was actually a TV miniseries. And that one did take place in the 50's. At least, for the scenes involving the cast as children.

The new one that came out (with Bill Skarsgård as Pennywise) moved the children's encounter timeframe up to the 1980's; that way there, when part II comes out, they can film it as happening in 2016 instead of the 1980s (as with the Tim Curry version).





